<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-06T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4593: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-06T11:00:00+01:00">March 6, 1932—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 6—7:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>56. Your 28, March 5, 9 p.m. When I dictated my 54, March 5, 2 p.m., I
                            made a slip of the tongue in dictating the word “local”. I had no
                            intention of differentiating between the Shanghai and Nanking
                            authorities. Please state urgently whether the idea thus amended by
                            providing consultation with Nanking meets with your approval. I should
                            like to be in possession of the information if possible Monday
                            morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_WHR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>